wikipedia_page.main: Noel Benjamin Sherwell (16 March 1904 – 29 December 1960) was an English first-class cricketer active 1923–39 who played 36 First-class matches for Middlesex and Cambridge University. He was born in Hendon, educated at Tonbridge School and Gonville & Caius College, Cambridge.  He died near Chur in Switzerland.
